DGM to Addl. Vice President/ Manufacturing
Cethar Limited

January 2007
To May 2014


India
6         Cethar Limited,  Trichy           DGM to Addl. Vice President/ Manufacturing   (From 2007 to till date)   Factory Incharge for the Boiler Components of 150 MW & above. (Unit-7)   6 years• 26 years of manufacturing experience to execute the Boiler Pressure & Non-Pressure Parts components to Boilers (Drums,  Headers,  Pipings,  Pressure Vessels,  Supporting Structures,  Industrial Fans,  Dampers,  Silencers etc.,  )• To transform Quality Plans / Quality Procedures into the products.• Shop Layout to suit product manufacturing sequence.• Planning,  Scheduling & Controlling.• Sub contracting,  Vendor evaluation & developments.• Conducting proactive meetings to plan and accomplish new products Quality requirements.• Resolving the Labor disputes.• Interaction with inter departments to resolve the issues with respect to the  manufacturing.• Estimation of cost of manufacturing and completion within the budget.• Empowerment and encouraging of the subordinates.• Team building up through motivational approach for safe quality production.• Familiar on Codes / Standards like IBR,  ASME and BS.• Successfully involved in ASME S,  U1 symbol certification audits.• Successfully involved in ISO 9001:2008.• Successfully involved in EMS: 14001 and OHSAS: 18001 certification audits and ensured the implementation of safety in the areas of working.• Training of personnel to impart special skills and up gradation of ability.• Identifying of norms for production in critical work centers to monitor productivity.• Implementation of ERP systems related to manufacturing activities (From Material receipt to completion of the job)PROFESSIONAL ACHIEVEMENTSErection & Commissioning:• Erected sub critical boilers ranging from Capacity 25 TPH to 125 TPH in various states which includes erection,  hydro testing and commissioning.• Liaised with Boiler Directorate,  Central Excise,  Sales Taxes and Labor Office in connection with the site fabrication,  Erection & commissioning of Boilers.• Involved in Welders Qualification Tests as per Indian Boiler Regulations - Chapter-XIIIContracts Management:• Co-ordination with Customer and Cethar (Commercial,  Engineering,  Quality Assurance & Control,  Procurement,  Finance,  Legal,  Erection & commissioning groups) and completion of the job as per the P.O.Manufacturing:• Process & Methods for the manufacturing of Condensers,  Pressure Vessels Boilers of various types & capacities of Industrial and Utility Boilers to a maximum capacity of 350 MW.• Erection & Commissioning of Critical Machines like Plate Rolling Machines for Cold and Hot rolling of high thicknesses,  Heat Treating Furnaces,  Saddle Drilling Machines to drill up to 100 mm dia holes drilling,  Pipe Bending Machines for Cold and Hot bending,  Pipe Chamfering Machines,  Band saw cutting Machines to cut P91 and SS materials,  STBW Machines & System Bending Machines for on line coil manufacturing meeting the specified quality requirements.• Involved in the implementation of Narrow Gap Welding in Drum circumferential seams manufactured large size headers for 500 MW capacity boilers and P91 piping (bending & welding of 2000 Tons) to M/s. BHEL.  Also fabricated drums to their Quality requirements.• Fabrication of Boiler drums,  152 mm / SA 299 material specification which were hot rolled and Submerged Arc welded.  These were the first 135 MW fabrications to international Quality,  Subsequently to 180 mm thickness to 350 MW capacity boilers.• Fabrication of Headers using P91 materials.• Fabricated Boiler Components for M/s. Metso oy / Finland to export boilers in Thailand,  Brazil,  China & India.• Fabricated Steam & Feed pipings of 625 Tons to M/s. Koniambo to be erected at New Calidonia as per European norms.  Obtained appreciation from this customer on ON TIME completion.• Fabrication of Shree Cements multi rowed (6 rows) modules for WHRB with the new operation process to minimal distortion.• Developed Engineers and Supervisors to take up the new jobs for M/s. BHEL like Drums,  Headers,  Piping and Coils with T91 material.• Successful fabrication of Aryan Coal 135 MW boiler columns in Unit-7.Recent Achievements:• Elimination of inside surface scale formation during Normalizing Heat treatment of Alloy steel Pipe Bends (SA335 P11,  P22 & P91) by simple Nitrogen Purging.Administrative skills:• Managed different type of personnel from our state and other states around 2000 workers and 250 staff.• Produced maximum 2500 tons per month pressure parts and 200 tons non pressure part components - fans and ducting.• Managed shops of covered area 20 acres,  three buildings with 13 bays.• Experienced in liaisoning the statutory and third party inspectors like IBR,  Lloyds,  TPL,  Metso,  TUV,  BV,  BHEL etc.• Co-ordinated with the statutory Authorities - Inspector of Factories,  Electrical Inspectorates,  Customs,  Central Excise dept.,  Pollution and Explosives agencies and other Labour office officials.• Developed the skill of managing the financial aspects of Production function through monthly P & L (Profit & Loss) statements.Vision of achievement in future:With Strong leadership Quality,  aim to lead reputed Company's profit centre.In general,  possessing high level of energy,  enthusiastic and healthy to take up challenge assignments as if a entrepreneur.DECLARATIONI hereby declare that the above informations are true in my knowledge.Place: Date: (B. BALAKRISHNAN)


